\subsection{Sync and async}{

Every request-making surface supports both a synchronous mode (returns a
\code{data.table}) and an asynchronous mode (returns a \link[promises:promise]{promises::promise} resolving
to the same \code{data.table}), selected by the \code{async} argument. See
\link{CensusBase} for the shared mechanism.
}

\subsection{The API key}{

Data queries require a Census API key (a free credential from
\url{https://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html}); the metadata/discovery
endpoints do not. Supply it as the \code{CENSUS_API_KEY} environment variable or
the \code{api_key} constructor argument. A newly issued key must be \strong{activated}
(via the confirmation email) before data queries succeed; until then the API
redirects data queries to an HTML error page, which this package surfaces as a
typed \link{census_conditions} error.
}
